---
title: Korean Fried Chicken with Charred Corn Slaw & Sriracha Mayonnaise
description: Korean cuisine isn’t shy about using big, bold, and outrageous flavours. Tonight's dish is no exception. It takes a cue from the Asian nation’s famed version of fried chicken, using a sweet, spicy, and savoury sauce to give them major personality. To complete the vibrant array on this plate, we’re adding a crisp slaw salad and a drizzle of creamy mayo.

*This recipe is under 650kcal per serving and under 30g carbohydrates per serving.*
